{"title_page": "Let's Play Two", "text_new": "{{short description|2017 live album by Pearl Jam}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{use American English|date=October 2017}}\n{{For|the catchphrase \"Let's play two!\"|Ernie Banks}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Let's Play Two\n| type       = live\n| artist     = [[Pearl Jam]]\n| cover      = Pearl Jam Let's Play Two.jpeg\n| released   = {{Start date|2017|09|29}} <small>(album)</small><br>{{Start date|2017|11|17}} <small>(film)</small>\n| recorded   = August 20 and 22, 2016\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]]\n| length     = 79:42\n| label      = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Lightning Bolt (Pearl Jam album)|Lightning Bolt]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Gigaton]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = The Daily Vault\n| rev1Score = B+<ref name=vault>{{cite web |url= http://dailyvault.com/toc.php5?review=9762 |title=The Daily Vault Music Reviews : Let's Play Two |first=Benjamin |last=Ray |work=dailyvault.com |year=2019 |accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Let's Play Two''''' is a live album and concert film by American alternative rock band [[Pearl Jam]]. The album was released on September 29, 2017, with the concert film being released on November 17, 2017.<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/pearl-jam-capture-wrigley-field-shows-in-lets-play-two-w498765 |title=Pearl Jam Capture Wrigley Field Shows in 'Let's Play Two' Concert Film |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Rolling Stone}}</ref><ref name=\"GW\">{{cite web |url=https://www.guitarworld.com/artist-news/pearl-jam-announce-lets-play-two-live-album-and-concert-film/31621 |title=Pearl Jam Announce \"Let's Play Two\" Live Album and Concert Film |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Guitar World}}</ref> The footage and songs were recorded at the band's shows at [[Wrigley Field]] during their [[Pearl Jam 2016 North America Tour|2016 tour]].<ref name=\"DL\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/pearl-jam-lets-play-two-movie-wrigley-field-concerts-1202153032/ |title=Pearl Jam Concert Docu \u2018Let\u2019s Play Two\u2019 Rocks Release Date |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Deadline}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n;Audio\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = \n| all_lyrics      = [[Eddie Vedder]], except where noted\n| title1          = Low Light\n| lyrics1         = Ament\n| music1          = Ament\n| length1         = 3:16\n| title2          = [[Better Man (Pearl Jam song)|Better Man]]\n| music2          = Vedder\n| length2         = 5:15\n| title3          = [[Elderly Woman Behind the Counter in a Small Town]]\n| music3          = Vedder\n| length3         = 3:26\n| title4          = Last Exit\n| music4          = [[Dave Abbruzzese]], [[Stone Gossard]]\n| length4         = 2:34\n| title5          = Lightning Bolt\n| music5          = Vedder\n| length5         = 5:42\n| title6          = Black, Red, Yellow\n| music6          = Vedder\n| length6         = 2:55\n| title7          = [[Black (Pearl Jam song)|Black]]\n| music7          = Gossard\n| length7         = 7:50\n| title8          = [[Corduroy (Pearl Jam song)|Corduroy]]\n| music8          = Vedder\n| length8         = 6:04\n| title9          = [[Given to Fly]]\n| music9          = [[Mike McCready]]\n| length9         = 3:25\n| title10         = [[Jeremy (song)|Jeremy]]\n| music10         = Ament\n| length10        = 5:01\n| title11         = Inside Job\n| lyrics11        = McCready\n| music11         = McCready, Vedder\n| length11        = 5:54\n| title12         = [[Go (Pearl Jam song)|Go]]\n| music12         = Abbruzzese\n| length12        = 2:49\n| title13         = Crazy Mary\n| lyrics13        = [[Victoria Williams]]\n| music13         = Williams\n| length13        = 6:22\n| title14         = Release \n| music14         = Ament, [[Dave Krusen]], Gossard, McCready, Vedder\n| length14        = 5:29\n| title15         = [[Alive (Pearl Jam song)|Alive]]\n| music15         = Gossard\n| length15        = 6:04\n| title16         = [[All the Way (Eddie Vedder song)|All the Way]]\n| music16         = Vedder\n| length16        = 4:02\n| title17         = [[I've Got a Feeling]]\n| lyrics17        = [[Lennon-McCartney]]\n| music17         = Lennon-McCartney\n| length17        = 3:36\n}}\n\n;Video\n# \"Low Light\"\n# \"Better Man\"\n# \"Elderly Woman Behind the Counter in a Small Town\"\n# \"Last Exit\"\n# \"Lightning Bolt\"\n# \"Black, Red, Yellow\"\n# \"Black\n# \"Corduroy\"\n# \"Given to Fly\"\n# \"Jeremy\"\n# \"Inside Job\"\n# \"Go\n# \"Crazy Mary\"\n# \"Release\"\n# \"Alive\"\n# \"All the Way\"\n# \"I've Got a Feeling\"\n\n'''Bonus tracks'''\n#\"Black\"\n# \"Mind Your Manners\"\n# \"[[Masters of War]]\"\n# \"[[Rearviewmirror]]\"\n# \"[[Immortality (Pearl Jam song)|Immortality]]\"\n# \"Lukin'\" <small>(hidden track)</small>\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Pearl Jam'''\n* [[Jeff Ament]] \u2013 bass guitar; backing vocals on \"Low Light\"\n* [[Matt Cameron]] \u2013 drums\n* [[Stone Gossard]] \u2013 rhythm (acoustic on \"Better Man\" and \"Small Town\") guitar; brief vocals on \"Better Man\"\n* [[Mike McCready]] \u2013 lead guitar; backing vocals on \"Low Light\"\n* [[Eddie Vedder]] \u2013 lead vocals, rhythm guitar\n\n'''Additional musicians'''\n* [[Boom Gaspar]] \u2013 [[Hammond organ]]\n\n'''Technical personnel'''\n* Ed Brooks \u2013 [[Audio mastering|mastering]]\n* John Burton \u2013 recording\n* [[Danny Clinch]] \u2013 [[liner notes]] and photos\n* Brett Eliason \u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n* Joe Spix \u2013 layout and design\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+Weekly sales chart performance for ''Let's Play Two''\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2017)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|45|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 7, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|55|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|25|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|51|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|48|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|France|136|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 17, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|37|id=341042|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 6, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland2|51|artist=Pearl Jam|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 7, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Italy|21|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 7, 2017}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| New Zealand Heatseeker Albums ([[Recorded Music NZ|RMNZ]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/albums?chart=4411|title=NZ Heatseekers Albums Chart|publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]]|date=October 16, 2017|accessdate=October 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n{{album chart|Portugal|7|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 17, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|45|date=20171006|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 7, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Spain|21|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 12, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|91|artist=Pearl Jam|album=Let's Play Two - Live at Wrigley Field|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 11, 2017}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|31|artist=Pearl Jam|rowheader=true|accessdate=October 10, 2017}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Pearl Jam |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:2017 soundtracks]]\n[[Category:Pearl Jam live albums]]\n[[Category:2017 live albums]]\n[[Category:Film soundtracks]]\n[[Category:2017 video albums]]\n[[Category:Wrigley Field]]\n[[Category:Pearl Jam video albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2017 live album by Pearl Jam}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2019}}\n{{use American English|date=October 2017}}\n{{For|the catchphrase \"Let's play two!\"|Ernie Banks}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Let's Play Two\n| type       = live\n| artist     = [[Pearl Jam]]\n| cover      = Pearl Jam Let's Play Two.jpeg\n| released   = {{Start date|2017|09|29}} <small>(album)</small><br>{{Start date|2017|11|17}} <small>(film)</small>\n| recorded   = August 20 and 22, 2016\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Alternative rock]]\n| length     = 79:42\n| label      = [[Republic Records|Republic]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = [[Lightning Bolt (Pearl Jam album)|Lightning Bolt]]\n| prev_year  = 2013\n| next_title = [[Gigaton]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = The Daily Vault\n| rev1Score = B+<ref name=vault>{{cite web |url= http://dailyvault.com/toc.php5?review=9762 |title=The Daily Vault Music Reviews : Let's Play Two |first=Benjamin |last=Ray |work=dailyvault.com |year=2019 |accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n'''''Let's Play Two''''' is a live album and concert film by American alternative rock band [[Pearl Jam]]. The album was released on September 29, 2017, with the concert film being released on November 17, 2017.<ref name=\"RS\">{{cite web |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/pearl-jam-capture-wrigley-field-shows-in-lets-play-two-w498765 |title=Pearl Jam Capture Wrigley Field Shows in 'Let's Play Two' Concert Film |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Rolling Stone}}</ref><ref name=\"GW\">{{cite web |url=https://www.guitarworld.com/artist-news/pearl-jam-announce-lets-play-two-live-album-and-concert-film/31621 |title=Pearl Jam Announce \"Let's Play Two\" Live Album and Concert Film |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Guitar World}}</ref> The footage and songs were recorded at the band's shows at [[Wrigley Field]] during their [[Pearl Jam 2016 North America Tour|2016 tour]].<ref name=\"DL\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/pearl-jam-lets-play-two-movie-wrigley-field-concerts-1202153032/ |title=Pearl Jam Concert Docu \u2018Let\u2019s Play Two\u2019 Rocks Release Date |accessdate=August 22, 2017 |work=Deadline}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n;Audio\n{{tracklist\n| total_length    = \n| all_lyrics      = [[Eddie Vedder]], except where noted\n| title1          = Low Light\n| lyrics1         = Ament\n| music1          = Ament\n| length1         = 3:16\n| title2          = [[Better Man (Pearl Jam song)|Better Man]]\n| music2          = Vedder\n| length2         = 5:15\n| title3          = [[Elderly Woman Behind the Counter in a Small Town]]\n| music3          = Vedder\n| length3         = 3:26\n| title4          = Last Exit\n| music4          = [[Dave Abbruzzese]], [[Stone Gossard]]\n| length4         = 2:34\n| title5          = Lightning Bolt\n| music5          = Vedder\n| length5         = 5:42\n| title6          = Black, Red, Yellow\n| music6          = Vedder\n| length6         = 2:55\n| title7          = [[Black (Pearl Jam song)|Black]]\n| music7          = Gossard\n| length7         = 7:50\n| title8          = [[Corduroy (Pearl Jam song)|Corduroy]]\n| music8          = Vedder\n| length8         = 6:04\n| title9          = [[Given to Fly]]\n| music9          = [[Mike McCready]]\n| length9         = 3:25\n| title10         = [[Jeremy (song)|Jeremy]]\n| music10         = Ament\n| length10        = 5:01\n| title11         = Inside Job\n| lyrics11        = McCready\n| music11         = McCready, Vedder\n| length11        = 5:54\n| title12         = [[Go (Pearl Jam song)|Go]]\n| music12         = Abbruzzese\n| length12        = 2:49\n| title13         = Crazy Mary\n| lyrics13        = [[Victoria Williams]]\n| music13         = Williams\n| length13  